<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Hawaiian_Pidgin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Further_reading">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><span class="citation book">Sally Stewart (2001-09-31). "Hawaiian English". <i>Lonely Planet USA Phrasebook</i>. Lonely Planet Publications. pp.&#160;262–266. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1-86450-182-0" title="Special:BookSources/1-86450-182-0">1-86450-182-0</a>.</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Hawaiian+English&amp;rft.atitle=Lonely+Planet+USA+Phrasebook&amp;rft.aulast=Sally+Stewart&amp;rft.au=Sally+Stewart&amp;rft.date=2001-09-31&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B262%26ndash%3B266&amp;rft.pub=Lonely+Planet+Publications&amp;rft.isbn=1-86450-182-0&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Hawaiian_Pidgin"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><span class="citation Journal">Speidel, Gisela E. (1981). "Language and reading: bridging the language difference for children who speak Hawaiian English". <i>Educational Perspectives</i> <b>20</b>: 23–30.</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Language+and+reading%3A+bridging+the+language+difference+for+children+who+speak+Hawaiian+English&amp;rft.jtitle=Educational+Perspectives&amp;rft.aulast=Speidel%2C+Gisela+E.&amp;rft.au=Speidel%2C+Gisela+E.&amp;rft.date=1981&amp;rft.volume=20&amp;rft.pages=23%E2%80%9330&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Hawaiian_Pidgin"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><span class="citation Journal">Speidel, G. E., Tharp, R. G., and Kobayashi, L. (1985). "Is there a comprehension problem for children who speak nonstandard English? A study of children with Hawaiian English backgrounds". <i>Applied Psycholinguistics</i> <b>6</b> (01): 83–96. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1017%2FS0142716400006020" class="external text" rel="nofollow">10.1017/S0142716400006020</a>.</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Is+there+a+comprehension+problem+for+children+who+speak+nonstandard+English%3F+A+study+of+children+with+Hawaiian+English+backgrounds&amp;rft.jtitle=Applied+Psycholinguistics&amp;rft.aulast=Speidel%2C+G.+E.%2C+Tharp%2C+R.+G.%2C+and+Kobayashi%2C+L.&amp;rft.au=Speidel%2C+G.+E.%2C+Tharp%2C+R.+G.%2C+and+Kobayashi%2C+L.&amp;rft.date=1985&amp;rft.volume=6&amp;rft.issue=01&amp;rft.pages=83%26ndash%3B96&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1017%2FS0142716400006020&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Hawaiian_Pidgin"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Hawaiian_Pidgin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="External_links">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.e-hawaii.com/fun/pidgin/default.asp" class="external text" rel="nofollow">e-Hawaii.com Searchable Pidgin English Dictionary</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.hawaii.edu/satocenter/" class="external text" rel="nofollow">The Charlene Sato Center for Pidgin, Creole and Dialect Studies</a>, a center devoted to pidgin, creole, and dialect studies at the University of Hawai<span class="okina">ʻ</span>i at Mānoa, Hawai<span class="okina">ʻ</span>i. Also home of the Pidgin Coup, a group of academics and community members interested in Hawai<span class="okina">ʻ</span>i Pidgin related research and education</li>
<li><a href="http://www.hawaii.edu/sls/pidgin.html" class="external text" rel="nofollow">Position Paper on Pidgin by the "Pidgin Coup"</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.pidginbible.org" class="external text" rel="nofollow">Da Hawai<span class="okina">ʻ</span>i Pidgin Bible</a> (see <i>Da Jesus Book</i> below)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.thesimplevoice.com" class="external text" rel="nofollow">The Simple Voice</a>, Hawaii pidgin poetry and commentary</li>
<li><a href="http://www.mauimagazine.net/Maui-Magazine//Department-Archive/index.php?tagID=249" class="external text" rel="nofollow">"Liddo Bitta Tita"</a> Hawaiian Pidgin column written by Tita, alter-ego of Kathy Collins. <i><a href="/wiki/Maui_No_Ka_%27Oi_Magazine" title="Maui No Ka 'Oi Magazine">Maui No Ka 'Oi Magazine</a></i> Vol.12 No.1 (Jan. 2008).</li>
<li><a href="http://www.mauimagazine.net/Maui-Magazine/January-February-2009/Dear-Prezadent-Obama/" class="external text" rel="nofollow">"Liddo Bitta Tita" audio file</a></li>
</ul>


